name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: mapreduce.job.speculative.minimum-allowed-tasks
description:
The minimum allowed tasks that
  can be speculatively re-executed at any time.

name: dfs.datanode.slow.io.warning.threshold.ms
description:
The threshold in milliseconds at which we will log a slow
    io warning in a datanode. By default, this parameter is set to 300
    milliseconds.

name: mapreduce.job.reducer.unconditional-preempt.delay.sec
description:
The threshold (in seconds) after which an unsatisfied
      mapper request triggers a forced reducer preemption irrespective of the
      anticipated headroom. By default, it is set to 5 mins. Setting it to 0
      leads to immediate reducer preemption. Setting to -1 disables this
      preemption altogether.

name: hadoop.security.groups.cache.secs
description:
This is the config controlling the validity of the entries in the cache
    containing the user->group mapping. When this duration has expired,
    then the implementation of the group mapping provider is invoked to get
    the groups of the user and then cached back.

name: dfs.namenode.delegation.token.max-lifetime
description:
The maximum lifetime in milliseconds for which a delegation 
      token is valid.

name: yarn.app.mapreduce.am.container.log.limit.kb
description:
The maximum size of the MRAppMaster attempt container logs in KB.
    0 disables the cap.

name: dfs.block.invalidate.limit
description:
The maximum number of invalidate blocks sent by namenode to a datanode
    per heartbeat deletion command. This property works with
    "dfs.namenode.invalidate.work.pct.per.iteration" to throttle block
    deletions.
